data.title: Actress Helen Fortescue Reynolds, Los Angeles, 1930s
data.meta_description: Access to this collection is generously supported by Arcadia funds.Actress Helen Fortescue Reynolds sits on chair. Reynolds was an American actress who appeared in films during the late 1930s and 1940s. She was also known as Helene Whitney, Helene Reynolds, and Joyce Gardner.Text from original nitrate sleeve: Reynolds, Helen Fortescue.Handwritten annotation from nitrate negative: Helen Fortescue Reynolds.
